# Commit Message Template (Conventional Style)
#
# Format:
# <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#
# Example:
# feat(sensor): add initial TOF sensor support
# fix(motor): correct direction reversal logic
# docs(readme): add platform badges
#
# ----------------------------
# <types>:
# feat:     New feature
# fix:      Bug fix
# docs:     Documentation
# style:    Formatting (no code logic changes)
# refactor: Code change without behavior change
# perf:     Performance improvement
# test:     Added or updated tests
# chore:    Build, tooling, infrastructure
# build:    Build system or dependencies
#
# ----------------------------
# <short summary>:
# One line, max ~70 characters. Present tense. No period at the end.
#
# <body> (optional):
# More details: what was done, why, and how
#
# <footer> (optional):
# e.g. Closes #123, Relates to #456
